17/05/2010
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- Fans of the Fenerbahce football club on Sunday (May 16th) went on a rampage in the stadium after, in an upset, their team failed to secure the Turkish league title in a match against Trabzon. Angry Fenerbahce's fans began smashing seats at the Sukru Saracoglu stadium in Istanbul and set them on fire. They threw bottles and stones at police, who used water cannons to disperse the crowd. There were several injuries and arrests. (Zaman, Vatan, Radikal - 17/05/10; Reuters, AP, Haber Turk - 16/05/10)
